obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (60321)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60321&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Dam Safety Act,`
  line 2021.
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `30th December, 2021, vide notification No. S.O.5422(E), dated 30th December, 2021, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3 (ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (60322)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration as to expediency of Union control.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60322&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that it is expedient in the`
  line `public interest that the Union should take under its control the regulation of uniform dam safety`
  line `procedure for specified dam to the extent hereinafter provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (60323)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Application.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60323&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Save as provided under this Act, it applies to the owner of every specified`
  line `dam, —`
  line
  line `(a) being a public sector undertaking or institution or a body owned or controlled by the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government or jointly by one or more Governments, as the case may be;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) being an undertaking or company or institution or a body other than those owned or`
  line `controlled by the State Government or the Central Government, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (60324)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60324&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "alteration" of dam means alterations or repairs as may directly affect the safety of the dam`
  line `or reservoir;`
  line
  line `(b) "annual report" means a report giving the activities of the Authority and the State Dam`
  line `Safety Organisation and the safety status of the specified dams falling under their jurisdiction`
  line `during each financial year;`
  line
  line `(c) "appurtenant" structure means the structure being---`
  line
  line `(i) spillways, either in the dam or separate therefrom;`
  line
  line `(ii) low level outlet structure and water conduits such as tunnels, pipelines or penstocks,`
  line `either through the dam or its abutments or reservoir rim;`
  line
  line `(iii) hydro-mechanical equipment including gate, valve, hoist, elevators;`
  line
  line `(iv) energy dissipation and river training structure; and`
  line
  line `(v) other associated structures acting integrally with the dam or its reservoir or reservoir rim;`
  line
  line `(d) "Authority" means the National Dam Safety Authority established under section 8;`
  line
  line `(e) "dam"means any artificial barrier and its appurtenant structure constructed across rivers or`
  line `tributaries thereof with a view to impound or divert water which also include barrage, weir and`
  line `similar water impounding structures but does not include---`
  line
  line `(a) canal, aquaduct, navigation channel and similar water conveyance structures;`
  line
  line `(b) flood embankment, dike, guide bund and similar flow regulation structures;`
  line
  line `(f) "dam failure" means any failure of the structure or operation of a dam which leads to`
  line `uncontrolled flow of impounded water resulting in downstream flooding, affecting the life and`
  line `property of the people and the environment including flora, fauna and riverine ecology.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this clause, failure in the operation shall mean such faulty`
  line `operations of the dam which are inconsistent with the operation and maintenance manual;`
  line
  line `(g) "dam incident" means all such problems occurring to a dam that have not degraded into a`
  line `dam failure, and includes---`
  line
  line `(i) any structural damage to the dam and the appurtenant structure;`
  line
  line `(ii) any unusual reading of any instrument in the dam;`
  line
  line `(iii) any unusual seepage or leakage through the dam body;`
  line
  line `(iv) any unusual change in the seepage or leakage regime;`
  line
  line `(v) any boiling or artesian condition noticed below the dam;`
  line
  line `(vi) any sudden stoppage or unusual reduction in seepage or leakage from the foundation or`
  line `body of the dam or any of its galleries;`
  line
  line `(vii) any malfunction or inappropriate operation of gates;`
  line
  line `(viii) occurrence of flood, the peak of which exceeds the available flood discharge capacity`
  line `of the dam or seventy per cent. of the approved design flood;`
  line
  line `(ix) occurrence of flood, which resulted in encroachment on the available freeboard, or the`
  line `approved design freeboard;`
  line
  line `(x) any unusual erosion in the near vicinity up to five hundred metres downstream of the`
  line `spillway or waste-weir; and`
  line
  line `(xi) any other occurrence which a prudent dam engineer may relate to dam safety concerns;`
  line
  line `(h) "dam safety unit" means a dam safety unit of any specified dam referred to in section 30;`
  line
  line `(i) "distress condition" means the occurrence or potential development of such conditions in the`
  line `dam or appurtenance structure or its reservoir or reservoir rim, which if left unattended to, may`
  line `impede the safe operation of dam for its intended benefits or may pose serious risks to the life and`
  line `property of people and the environment including flora, fauna and riverine ecology;`
  line
  line `(j) "documentation" means all permanent records including electronic records concerning`
  line `investigation, design, construction, operation, performance, maintenance, major repair, alteration,`
  line `enlargement and safety of dams and includes design memorandum, construction drawings,`
  line `geological reports, reports of specialised studies simulating structural and hydraulic response of the`
  line `dam, changes made in design and drawings, quality control records, emergency action plan,`
  line `operation and maintenance manual, instrumentation readings, inspection and testing reports,`
  line `operational reports, and dam safety review reports and other similar reports;`
  line
  line `(k) "enlargement of dam" means any change in the scope of an existing dam or reservoir, which`
  line `raises water storage elevation or increases the volume of water impounded by the dam;`
  line
  line `(l)"Government" means the Central Government or a State Government, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(m) "inspection" means on-site examination of any component of a dam and its appurtenant`
  line structure;
  line
  line `(n) "investigation" means collection of evidence, detailed examination, analysis or scrutiny of a`
  line `specific problem pertaining to the dam and its appurtenant or a part thereof and includes laboratory`
  line `testing, in-situ testing, geological exploration, model testing and mathematical simulation of the`
  line problem;
  line
  line `(o) "National Committee" means the National Committee on Dam Safety constituted`
  line `under section 5;`
  line
  line `(p) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the term notify`
  line `shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(q) "operation of dam" means elements of the use, control and functioning of the dam which`
  line `may primarily affect the storage, release of water and the structural safety of the dam;`
  line
  line `(r) "operation and maintenance manual" means the written instructions that provide operation`
  line `procedures, maintenance procedures, emergency procedures and any other features necessary for`
  line `the safe operation of dam;`
  line
  line `(s) "owner of specified dam" means the Central Government or a State Government or jointly`
  line `by one or more Governments or public sector undertaking or local authority or company and any or`
  line `all of such persons or organisations, who own, control, operate, or maintain a specified dam;`
  line
  line `(t) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the Central Government or, as the case may`
  line `be, by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(u) "regulations" means the regulations made by the Authority under this Act;`
  line
  line `(v)"remedial measures" means such structural or non-structural measures, as may be required in`
  line `relation to the specified dam or appurtenant structure or reservoir or reservoir rim or catchment`
  line `area of reservoir for the purpose of removing or mitigating the distress condition of the specified`
  line dam;
  line
  line `(w) "reservoir" in relation to a dam shall mean any spread of water impounded by a specified`
  line dam;
  line
  line `(x) "specified dam" means a dam constructed before or after the commencement of this Act,`
  line `which is,---`
  line
  line `(i) above fifteen metres in height, measured from the lowest portion of the general`
  line `foundation area to the top of dam; or`
  line
  line `(ii) between ten metres to fifteen metres in height and satisfies at least one of the following,`
  line `namely: ---`
  line
  line `(A) the length of crest is not less than five hundred metres; or`
  line
  line `(B) the capacity of the reservoir formed by the dam is not less than one million cubic`
  line `metres; or`
  line
  line `(C) the maximum flood discharge dealt with by the dam is not less than two thousand`
  line `cubic metres per second; or`
  line
  line `(D) the dam has specially difficult foundation problems; or`
  line
  line `(E) the dam is of unusual design;`
  line
  line `(y) "State Committee" means the State Committee on Dam Safety constituted under sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(z) "State Dam Safety Organisation" means the State Dam Safety Organisation established`
  line `under section 14; and`
  line
  line `(za) "vulnerability and hazard classification" means the system or systems of classifying dams`
  line `on the basis of their condition, location, damage or hazard potential.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (60325)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Constitution of National Committee..`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60325&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, appoint, there shall be constituted, for the purposes of this Act, a`
  line `National Committee to be known as the National Committee on Dam Safety consisting of the`
  line `following members, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairman, Central Water Commission---Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) not exceeding ten representatives of the Central Government not below the rank of Joint`
  line `Secretary to that Government or equivalent dealing with matters relating to dam engineering or`
  line `dam safety, nominated by the Central Government---Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) not exceeding seven representatives of the State Governments of the level of Engineer-inChief or equivalent by rotation, nominated by the Central Government---Members, ex officio; and`
  line
  line `(d) not exceeding three specialists in the field of dam safety and allied fields nominated by the`
  line `Central Government---Members.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Committee shall be constituted within a period of sixty days from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act, and shall be reconstituted for every three years thereafter.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (60326)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Functions of National Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60326&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Committee shall discharge such`
  line `functions as specified in the First Schedule as may be necessary to prevent dam failure related`
  line `disasters and to maintain standards of dam safety.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Committee may, in discharge of its functions, constitute such sub-committees as it`
  line `may consider necessary to assist it and the secretarial assistance to the National Committee and the`
  line `sub-committees shall be provided by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) The knowledge and information collected or generated by the National Committee shall be`
  line `disseminated to all stakeholders by the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (60327)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Meetings of National Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60327&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Committee shall meet at such times and`
  line `places and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings`
  line `in the manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the National Committee shall meet twice in a year and one meeting shall be held`
  line `before the onset of the monsoon season.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Committee may invite the representative of the owner of any specified dam and`
  line `such other experts in dam safety (including international experts) as it may consider appropriate for the`
  line `discharge of its functions.`
  line
  line `(3) The expenditure incurred on the National Committee shall be in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (60328)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Establishment of National Dam Safety Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60328&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the`
  line `Central Government may by notification, appoint, there shall be established for the purposes of this`
  line `Act, a National Dam Safety Authority, within a period of sixty days from the date of commencement`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall be headed by an officer not below the rank of Additional Secretary to the`
  line `Government of India or equivalent to be appointed by the Central Government who have knowledge`
  line `of, and adequate qualification, experience and capacity in, dealing with problems relating to the dam`
  line `engineering and dam safety management.`
  line
  line `(3) The headquarters of the Authority shall be at the National Capital territory of Delhi and the`
  line `Authority may establish offices at other places in India.`
  line
  line `(4) The Authority shall comply with such directions as may, from time to time, be given to it by the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (60329)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Functions of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60329&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall discharge such functions as specified in the`
  line `Second Schedule as may be necessary to implement the policy, guidelines and standards evolved by`
  line `the National Committee for proper surveillance, inspection and maintenance of specified dams and for`
  line `such purposes, it shall have the power to enforce the attendance of any person and call for any`
  line `information as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), the Authority shall make all`
  line `endeavours to resolve any issue between the State Dam Safety Organisations of States or between a`
  line `State Dam Safety Organisation and any owner of a specified dam in that State.`
  line
  line `(3) Every decision of the Authority taken in respect of matters under this Act shall be final and`
  line `binding upon all the parties to the issue.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (60330)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Officers and Employees of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60330&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, for the purpose of`
  line `enabling the Authority to perform functions under this Act, provide such number of officers and other`
  line `employees as it may consider necessary:`
  line
  line `Provided that the officers and other employees shall have such qualifications and experience in the`
  line `field of dam safety including dam-design, hydro-mechanical engineering, hydrology, geo-technical`
  line `investigation, instrumentation, dam-rehabilitation or such other fields as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The functions, powers, terms and conditions of service of the officers and other employees`
  line `appointed under sub-section (1) shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (60331)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Constitution of State Committee on Dam Safety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60331&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the`
  line `State Government may, by notification, appoint, there shall be constituted, for the purposes of this Act,`
  line `a State Committee on Dam Safety consisting of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Engineer-in-Chief or equivalent officer of the Department of the State responsible for`
  line `Dam Safety--Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) technical and scientific officers of the rank of Chief Engineer, not exceeding six persons,`
  line `from such Departments as may be decided by the State Government or from such other`
  line `organisations owing specified dams--Members;`
  line
  line `(c) the Chief Engineer or equivalent level officer of each such upstream States in cases where`
  line `reservoir area of any of the specified dam of the State extends to another State--Members;`
  line
  line `(d) the Chief Engineer or equivalent level officer of each such downstream State in cases where`
  line `flood release of any of the specified dam of the State flows to a neighbouring State Members;`
  line
  line `(e) one representative of the Central Water Commission not below the rank of Director to be`
  line `nominated by the Chairman, Central Water Commission--Member;`
  line
  line `(f) experts in the field of hydrology or dam designs, not exceeding three, from engineering`
  line `institutes--Members; and`
  line
  line `(g) one representative of the Central Electricity Authority not below the rank of Director to be`
  line `nominated by the Chairman, Central Electricity Authority--Member.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Committee shall be constituted within a period of hundred and eighty days from the`
  line `date of commencement of this Act, and reconstituted for every three years thereafter.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (60332)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Functions of State Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60332&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Committee shall discharge such functions as`
  line `specified in the Third Schedule as may be necessary to prevent dam failure related disasters under this`
  line `Act as per guidelines, standards and other directions on dam safety issued by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Committee, in discharge of its functions, shall be assisted by such sub-committees as`
  line `it may consider necessary, and the secretarial assistance to the State Committee as well as its subcommittees shall be provided by the concerned State Dam Safety Organisation.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (60333)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Meetings of State Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60333&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Committee shall meet at such times and places`
  line `and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings as`
  line `may be prescribed by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Committee shall meet twice in a year and one meeting shall be held before the`
  line `onset of the monsoon season.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Committee may invite the representative of the owner of any specified dam and such`
  line `other experts in Dam Safety as it may consider appropriate, for the discharge of its functions.`
  line
  line `(3) The expenditure incurred on the meetings of the State Committee shall be in the manner as may`
  line `be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The specialist members and other expert invitees who attend the meetings of the State`
  line `Committee or its sub-committees shall be paid such fees and allowances as may be prescribed by the`
  line `State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (60334)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Establishment of State Dam Safety Organisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60334&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, by notification, establish in the Department dealing with dam safety, a separate`
  line `organisation, to be known as the State Dam Safety Organisation, within a period of hundred and eighty`
  line `days from the date of commencement of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that in States having more than thirty specified dams, the State Dam Safety Organisation`
  line `shall be headed by an officer not below the rank of Chief Engineer or equivalent, and in all other`
  line `cases, the State Dam Safety Organisation shall be headed by an officer not below the rank of`
  line `Superintendent Engineer or equivalent.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Dam Safety Organisation shall be responsible to, and report to, the technical head of`
  line `the Department dealing with Dam Safety.`
  line
  line `(3) The organisational structure and work procedures of the State Dam Safety Organisation shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The administrative and other expenses of the State Dam Safety Organisation shall be borne by`
  line `the respective State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (60335)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Officers and employees of State Dam Safety Organisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60335&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government`
  line `shall, having regard to the number of specified dams in that State, provide such number of officers and`
  line `employees to the State Dam Safety Organisation as it may consider necessary for the efficient`
  line `functioning of the said Organisation:`
  line
  line `Provided that the officers and employees shall have such qualifications and experience in the field`
  line `of dam safety including dam-design, hydro-mechanical engineering, hydrology, geo-technical`
  line `investigation, instrumentation, dam-rehabilitation or such other field as may be prescribed by the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) The functions and powers of the officers and employees appointed under sub-section (1) shall`
  line `be such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (60336)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Surveillance and inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60336&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Dam Safety Organisation shall,---`
  line
  line `(a) keep perpetual surveillance;`
  line
  line `(b) carry out inspections; and`
  line
  line `(c) monitor the operation and maintenance,`
  line
  line `of all specified dams falling under their jurisdiction to ensure continued safety of such specified dams`
  line `and take such measures as may be necessary to address safety concerns that are noticed with a view to`
  line `achieve satisfactory level of dam safety assurance as per such guidelines, standards and other`
  line `directions on dam safety as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Dam Safety Organisation, for the purpose of enabling it to make decisions compatible`
  line `with public safety, shall make or cause to be made such investigations and shall gather or cause to be`
  line `gathered such data as may be required for proper review and study of the various features of the`
  line `design, construction, repair and enlargement of dams, reservoirs and appurtenant structures under their`
  line jurisdiction.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (60337)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Vulnerability and hazard classification of dams.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60337&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The State Dam Safety Organisation shall`
  line `classify each dam under their jurisdiction as per such vulnerability and hazard classification criteria as`
  line `may be specified by the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (60338)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Maintenance of log books.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60338&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Dam Safety Organisation shall maintain a log`
  line `book or database for each specified dam under their jurisdiction recording therein all activities related`
  line `to the surveillance and inspection and all important events related to dam safety and with such details`
  line `and in such form as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) Every State Dam Safety Organisation shall furnish all such information to the Authority as and`
  line `when required by them.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (60339)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Records of dam failures and dam incidents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60339&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Dam Safety Organisation shall`
  line `report the event of any dam failure under their jurisdiction to the Authority, and furnish any`
  line `information as and when required by them.`
  line
  line `(2) Every State Dam Safety Organisation shall maintain the records of major dam incidents of each`
  line `specified dams under their jurisdiction, and furnish all such information to the Authority as and when`
  line `required by them.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (60340)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Instructions on safety of specified dams.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60340&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Dam Safety Organisation shall`
  line `render its instructions to the owner of a specified dam on the safety or the remedial measures required`
  line `to be taken with respect to it.`
  line
  line `(2) Every owner of the specified dam shall comply with the instructions issued by the State Dam`
  line `Safety Organisation with regard to safety or remedial measures in relation to any specified dam owned`
  line `by it.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (60341)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Funds for maintenance and repairs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60341&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Every owner of the specified dam shall earmark`
  line `sufficient and specific funds for maintenance and repairs of the specified dam and to implement the`
  line `recommendations of the State Dam Safety Organisation.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (60342)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Technical documentation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60342&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every owner of the specified dam shall compile all technical`
  line `documentations concerning hydrology, dam foundation, structural engineering of dam, watershed`
  line `upstream of dam, and nature or use of land downstream of dam along with information on all`
  line `resources or facilities of economic, logistic or environmental importance which are likely to be`
  line `affected due to dam failure.`
  line
  line `(2) Every owner of the specified dam shall furnish all such information to the State Dam Safety`
  line `Organisation and the Authority as and when required by them.`
  line
  line `(3) Every owner of the specified dam shall equip its organisation with the state-of-the-art`
  line `information technology tools to store, retrieve, and distribute the data related to the dam safety and`
  line `dam performance.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (60343)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Qualifications and experience of individuals responsible for safety of specified dams.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60343&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Every individual responsible for safety of specified dams and all activities related thereto shall possess`
  line `such qualifications and experience and shall undergo such training as may be specified by the`
  line regulations.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (60344)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Jurisdiction of State Dam Safety Organisation and Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60344&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, all specified dams, shall fall under the jurisdiction of the State Dam Safety`
  line `Organisation of the State in which such dam is situated in matters relating to dam inspections, analysis`
  line `of information, investigation reports or recommendations regarding safety status, and remedial`
  line `measures to be undertaken to improve dam safety; and in all such matters, full co-operation shall be`
  line `extended by the owner of the specified dam:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a specified dam is owned by a Central Public Sector Undertaking or where a`
  line `specified dam is extended over two or more States, or where the specified dam in one State is owned`
  line `by another State, then the Authority shall be construed as the State Dam Safety Organisation for the`
  line `purposes of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in all such dams where the Authority takes up the role of State Dam Safety`
  line `Organisation, the Governments of the States within the jurisdiction of which such dams are located`
  line `shall have access to all information relating to these specified dams as available with the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The authorised representative of the Authority or concerned State Dam Safety Organisation for`
  line `the purposes of making any inspection or investigation necessary for the implementation of the`
  line `provisions of this Act, may enter upon any part of the specified dam or its site as and when required`
  line `and apply such investigation methods, as may be considered necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) After making inspection or investigation under sub-section (2), the representative referred to in`
  line `that sub-section is of the opinion that certain remedial measures are required to be taken, he shall`
  line `report such remedial measures to the officer-in-charge of such specified dam and to the concerned`
  line `State Dam Safety Organisation.`
  line
  line `(4) The Authority and concerned State Dam Safety Organisation, in cases of specified dams being`
  line `found to be distressed on account of their age, degeneration, degradation, structural or other`
  line `impediments, shall suggest such remedial measures on such operational parameters (including`
  line `maximum reservoir level, maximum spillway discharge and maximum discharges through other`
  line `outlets) as it may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing contained in sub-sections (1), (2), (3) and (4) shall absolve the owner of specified dam`
  line `or any other authority or person from any of the responsibilities or obligations entrusted upon it under`
  line `the provisions of this Act and the provisions of sub-sections (1), (2), (3) and (4) shall be in addition to,`
  line `and not in derogation of, any other provision of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (60345)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Cost of investigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60345&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `All the costs to be incurred by the Authority or State Dam Safety`
  line `Organisation on any form of investigation done including payment given to any consultant or expert,`
  line `shall be borne by the owner of the specified dam.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (60346)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Construction or alteration of dams.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60346&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any construction or alteration of a specified dam`
  line `shall be undertaken subject to investigation, design and construction being done by such agencies as`
  line `may be accredited by the Authority or the State Government, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority may disqualify any agency which violates any of the provisions of this`
  line `Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) Every agency referred to in sub-section (1) shall, for the purpose of designing or evaluating the`
  line `safety of the specified dam, make use of the relevant standard codes and guidelines of the Bureau of`
  line `Indian Standards, and furnish the reasons, if any departure is made in the design or dam safety`
  line evaluation.
  line
  line `(3) Every agency referred to in sub-section (1) shall for the purpose of investigation, design and`
  line `construction employ such qualified, experienced and competent engineers, as may be specified by the`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(4) Every agency referred to in sub-section (1) shall for the purpose of approval of dam design`
  line `demonstrate the safety of the design, operational parameters and policies as per the provisions of`
  line `relevant codes and guidelines to the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) Every agency referred to in sub-section (1) shall, for the purpose of dam construction,`
  line `undertake such quality control measures, as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(6) The construction of any specified dam or the alteration or enlargement of any existing specified`
  line `dam shall be undertaken with the approval of such competent authority, as may be specified by`
  line `notification by the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (60347)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Initial filling of reservoirs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60347&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Before initial filling of any reservoir of a specified dam, the`
  line `agency responsible for its design shall draw the filling criteria and prepare an initial filling plan, with`
  line `adequate time for monitoring and evaluating the performance of the dam and its appurtenant`
  line structures.
  line
  line `(2) Before initial filling of the reservoir is taken up, the State Dam Safety Organisation shall`
  line `inspect or cause to be inspected the specified dam either through its own engineers or by an`
  line `independent panel of experts, who shall also examine the initial filling programme and prepare a`
  line `detailed report thereof duly certifying the fitness of dam for filling.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (60348)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Operation and maintenance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60348&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every owner of the specified dam shall provide operation`
  line `and maintenance establishment for the specified dam, and shall ensure that sufficient number of`
  line `trained operation and maintenance engineers or technical persons are posted at each such dam.`
  line
  line `(2) Every owner of the specified dam shall ensure that a well-documented operation and`
  line `maintenance manual is kept at each of the specified dams and are followed at all times.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (60349)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Responsibility of owner of specified dam.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60349&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act shall be construed`
  line `to absolve an owner of a specified dam of the duties, obligations or liabilities incidental to the`
  line `construction, operation, maintenance and supervision of the dam or reservoir.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (60350)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Dam safety unit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60350&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `For each specified dam, the owner shall, within the operation and`
  line `maintenance establishment, provide a dam safety unit consisting of such competent levels of engineers`
  line `as may be specified by the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (60351)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title Inspection.
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60351&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every owner of a specified dam shall undertake every year, through their dam`
  line `safety unit, a pre-monsoon and post-monsoon inspections in respect of each such dam.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to sub-section (1), every owner of a specified dam shall inspect or cause to`
  line `be inspected every specified dam by the dam safety unit, during and after every flood, earthquake or`
  line `any other natural or man-made calamities, or if any sign of distress or unusual behaviour is noticed in`
  line `the dam.`
  line
  line `(3) Every owner of a specified dam shall, —`
  line
  line `(a) carry out all inspections referred to in sub-section (1) and sub-section (2) in accordance with`
  line `the guidelines and check-lists as may be specified by the regulations;`
  line
  line `(b) station, at each of the specified dam site throughout the monsoon period, such engineers and`
  line `other technical personnel, as may be decided, in consultation with the State Dam Safety`
  line `Organisation:`
  line
  line `Provided that the engineers and other technical personnel shall be required to be stationed at their`
  line `respective dam sites during entire period of emergency following any other natural or man-made`
  line `calamity that may create distress conditions in the dam; and`
  line
  line `(c) forward the inspection report by the dam safety unit to the State Dam Safety Organisation,`
  line `which shall analyse the report and submit comments on the deficiency and remedial measures, if any,`
  line `to the owner of the specified dam.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (60352)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Instrumentations to be installed in every specified dam.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60352&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every owner of a specified dam`
  line `shall have a minimum number of such instrumentations at each specified dam, and installed in such`
  line `manner as may be specified by the regulations for monitoring the performance of such dam.`
  line
  line `(2) Every owner of the specified dam shall maintain a record of readings of the instrumentations`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) and forward the analysis of such readings to the State Dam Safety`
  line `Organisation, in the form, manner and at such interval as may be specified by the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (60353)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Establishment of hydro-meteorological station.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60353&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every owner of a specified dam shall`
  line `establish a hydro-meteorological station in the vicinity of each specified dam capable of recording such`
  line `data as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) Every owner of the specified dam shall collect compile process and store data referred to in subsection (1) at a suitable location.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (60354)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Installations of seismological station.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60354&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the case of every specified dam, having a height`
  line `of thirty metres or above or falling under such seismic zone, as may be specified by the regulations, the`
  line `owner of the specified dam shall establish a seismological station in the vicinity of each such dam for`
  line `recording micro and strong motion earthquakes and such other data as may be specified by the`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(2) Every owner of a specified dam shall collect,compile,process and store data referred to in subsection (1) at such suitable location and in such manner as may be specified by the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (60355)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Obligation of owner of specified dam.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60355&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every owner of a specified dam, in respect of each`
  line `specified dam, shall, —`
  line
  line `(a) establish well designed hydro-meteorological network and an inflow forecasting system;`
  line
  line `(b) establish an emergency flood warning system for the probable flood affected areas`
  line `downstream of the dam;`
  line
  line `(c) test or cause to be tested periodically the functioning of systems referred to in clauses (a)`
  line `and (b);`
  line
  line `(d) install such scientific and technical instruments which are invented or adopted from time to`
  line `time for the purpose of ensuring the dam safety and the life and property of people downstream;`
  line
  line `(e) make available the information relating to maximum anticipated inflows and outflows`
  line `including flood warning and an adverse impact of the same, if any, on persons and property towards`
  line `the upstream or downstream of the dam, to the concerned district authorities and also make available`
  line `the information in public domain; and`
  line
  line `(f) render necessary assistance to the Authority in establishment and running of the early warning`
  line `system for the exchange of real time hydrological and meteorological data and information related to`
  line `the operation of reservoirs.`
  line
  line `(2) Every owner of a specified dam, for each of its dam shall, carry out risk assessment studies at`
  line `such interval as may be specified by the regulations and the first such study shall be made within five`
  line `years from the date of commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (60356)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Emergency action plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60356&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every owner of a specified dam, in respect of each of specified`
  line `dam, shall,---`
  line
  line `(a) prepare emergency action plan before allowing the initial filling of the reservoir and thereafter`
  line `update such plans at regular intervals;`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of the dam which is constructed and filled before the commencement of this Act,`
  line `prepare emergency action plan within five years from the date of commencement of this Act and`
  line `thereafter update such plans at regular intervals as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The emergency action plan referred to in sub-section (1) shall,---`
  line
  line `(a) set out the procedures to be followed for the protection of persons and property upstream or`
  line `downstream of the specified dam in the event of an actual or imminent dam failure or to mitigate the`
  line `effects of the disaster;`
  line
  line `(b) include therein,---`
  line
  line `(i) the type of emergencies which are likely to occur in the operation of any reservoir;`
  line
  line `(ii) identification of the likely catastrophic flood in the event of any dam failure, along with`
  line `probable areas, population, structures and installations likely to be adversely affected due to flood`
  line `water released from the reservoir;`
  line
  line `(iii) warning procedures, inundation maps and advance preparations for handling efficiently`
  line `and in the best possible manner the likely adverse situations especially to avoid loss of human`
  line life;
  line
  line `(iv) such other matters which may having regard to the geographical conditions, size of the`
  line `dam and other relevant factors as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) The emergency action plan under this section shall be put into action as and when conditions`
  line `arise which are hazardous or likely to be hazardous to a specified dam or potentially hazardous to public`
  line `safety, infrastructure, other property or to the environment.`
  line
  line `(4) Every owner of the specified dam shall, while preparing and updating the emergency action plan,`
  line `undertake a consultation process with all disaster management agencies and other Departments of the`
  line `State entrusted with disaster management and relief in the area likely to be affected and owners of other`
  line `dams in the immediate vicinity likely to be affected, so as to bring coordination and transparency and`
  line `allay any unwarranted fear on dam safety issues.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (60357)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Assistance to other disaster management authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60357&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the provisions of`
  line `this Act or liability of the owner of the specified dam and other organisations and authorities under this`
  line `Act, every owner, organisation and authority shall render necessary assistance, if so required by any`
  line `authority under any law for the time being in force to meet or mitigate any disaster or emergency arising`
  line `out of the specified dams.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (60358)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Comprehensive dam safety evaluation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60358&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner of a specified dam shall make or cause`
  line `to be made comprehensive dam safety evaluation of each specified dam through an independent panel`
  line `of experts constituted as per regulations for the purpose of determining the conditions of the specified`
  line `dam and its reservoir:`
  line
  line `Provided that the first comprehensive dam safety evaluation for each existing specified dam shall be`
  line `conducted within five years from the date of commencement of this Act, and thereafter the`
  line `comprehensive dam safety evaluation of each such dam shall be carried out at regular intervals as may`
  line `be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The comprehensive dam safety evaluation shall consists of, but not be limited to,---`
  line
  line `(a) review and analysis of available data on the design, construction, operation, maintenance and`
  line `performance of the structure;`
  line
  line `(b) general assessment of hydrologic and hydraulic conditions with mandatory review of design`
  line `floods as specified by the regulations;`
  line
  line `(c) general assessment of seismic safety of specified dam with mandatory site specific seismic`
  line `parameters study in certain cases as specified by the regulations;`
  line
  line `(d) evaluation of the operation, maintenance and inspection procedures; and`
  line
  line `(e) evaluation of any other conditions which constitute a hazard to the integrity of the structure.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (60359)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Compulsory evaluation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60359&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The comprehensive dam safety evaluation referred`
  line `to in section 38 shall be compulsory in the case of, —`
  line
  line `(a) major modification to the original structure or design criteria;`
  line
  line `(b) discovery of an unusual condition at the dam or reservoir rim; and`
  line
  line `(c) an extreme hydrological or seismic event`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (60360)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Reports of comprehensive evaluation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60360&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner of a specified dam shall report the`
  line `results of the dam safety evaluation undertaken under section 38 or section 39 to the State Dam Safety`
  line Organisation.
  line
  line `(2) The reports referred to in sub-section (1) shall include, but not be limited to, —`
  line
  line `(a) assessment of the condition of the structure based on the visual observations and available`
  line `data on the design, hydrology, construction, operation, maintenance and performance of the`
  line structure;
  line
  line `(b) recommendations for any emergency measures or actions, if required, to assure the`
  line `immediate safety of the structure;`
  line
  line `(c) recommendations for remedial measures and actions related to design, construction,`
  line `operation, maintenance and inspection of the structure, if required;`
  line
  line `(d) recommendations for additional detailed studies, investigations and analysis, if required; and`
  line
  line `(e) recommendations for improvements in routine maintenance and inspection of dam, if`
  line required.
  line
  line `(3) Where the safety evaluations undertaken under section 38 or section 39, results in`
  line `recommendations for a remedial action, the State Dam Safety Organisation shall pursue with the owner`
  line `of the specified dam to ensure that remedial measures are carried out in time, for which the owner shall`
  line `provide adequate funds.`
  line
  line `(4) Where there is any unresolved matter emerging between an independent panel of experts referred`
  line `to in sub section (1) of section 38 and the owner of the specified dam, the matter shall be referred to the`
  line `State Dam Safety Organisation, and, in case no agreement is arrived at, the matter shall be referred to`
  line `the Authority which shall render its advice and send recommendations to the State Government`
  line `concerned for implementation.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (60361)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Punishment for obstruction, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60361&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, without reasonable cause, —`
  line
  line `(a) obstructs any officer or employee of the Central Government or the State Government, or a`
  line `person authorised by the National Committee or the Authority or the State Committee or the State`
  line `Dam Safety Organisation in the discharge of his functions under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) refuses to comply with any direction given by or on behalf of the Central Government or the`
  line `State Government or the National Committee or the Authority or the State Committee or the State`
  line `Dam Safety Organisation under this Act, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to one year or with fine, or with both, and if such obstruction or refusal to comply with`
  line `directions results in loss of lives or imminent danger thereof, shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to two years.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (60362)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Offences by Departments of Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60362&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a Department of the Government, the head of the Department shall be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly unless he`
  line `proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all due diligence to`
  line `prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has`
  line `been committed by a Department of the Government and it is proved that the offence has been`
  line `committed with the consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any`
  line `officer, other than the head of the Department, such officer shall be deemed to be guilty of that offence`
  line `and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (60363)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Offence by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60363&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company or body corporate, every person who at the time the offence was committed, was in charge`
  line `of, and was responsible to, the company, for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the`
  line `company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the contravention and shall be liable to be proceeded against`
  line `and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any punishment`
  line `provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he`
  line `exercised due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has`
  line `been committed by a company, and it is proved that the offence was committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also, be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purpose of this section---`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (60364)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60364&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under`
  line `this Act, except on a complaint made by the Central Government or the State Government or a person`
  line `authorised in this behalf by the National Committee or the Authority or the State Committee or the`
  line `State Dam Safety Organisation, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class`
  line `shall try any offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (60365)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Annual report of safety status of specified dam.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60365&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Dam Safety Organisation`
  line `shall prepare annual report, within three months of the expiry of the preceding financial year, of its`
  line `activities and safety status of specified dams in the State and such report shall be forwarded to the`
  line `Authority and State Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of the State Legislature, where it consists of two Houses or where such Legislature consists of`
  line `one House, before that House.`
  line
  line `(2) Every State Dam Safety Organisation and every owner of a specified dam shall provide to the`
  line `Authority, documentation of the projects, report of enquiries into failure and any other data, as and`
  line `when required in such format and in such manner as may be decided by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority, shall prepare a consolidated annual report of the dam safety activities in the`
  line `country and submit the same to the Central Government within six months of the expiry of the`
  line `preceding financial year and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each House of`
  line Parliament.
  line
  line `(4) The Authority shall forward its annual report on the safety status of specified dams to the`
  line `National Disaster Management Authority and also make available such report in public domain.`
  line
  line `(5) The State Dam Safety Organisation of each State shall forward their annual report to the`
  line `concerned State Disaster Management Authority and also make available such report in public`
  line domain.
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (60366)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Safety measures in respect of dams other than specified dams.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60366&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Every owner of the dam`
  line `other than specified dams shall undertake such measures as may be necessary to ensure dam safety and`
  line `shall comply with such measures as may be specified by the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (60367)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Safety measures in respect of dams located outside territory of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60367&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `Where a dam,`
  line `including a dam created due to landslides or glacial moraine, is located outside the territory of India`
  line `and the Authority suo motu or on receipt of information from any person or organisation or authority`
  line `or source prima facie is of the opinion that measures are required to be taken to ensure safety of such`
  line `dams and failure of which may endanger the life and property of people located in India, it shall in`
  line `writing submit an intimation thereof to the Central Government indicating therein the likely damages`
  line `which may arise due to failure of such dams and the safety measures required to be taken in respect of`
  line `such dam and the Central Government shall take all suitable measures to mitigate any possible threat.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (60368)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60368&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (60369)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Power to amend Schedules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60369&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do, it may, by notification, amend the First Schedule, the Second Schedule or the Third`
  line `Schedule and thereupon the Schedules, shall be deemed to have been amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification made under sub-section (1) shall be laid before each House of`
  line `Parliament as soon as may be after it is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (60370)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60370&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give such`
  line `directions, as it may consider necessary, to the State Government where that Government is the owner`
  line `of the specified dam and to the owner of a specified dam in any other case for the effective`
  line `implementation of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (60377)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of National Committee on Dam Safety Authority and State Committee on Dam Safety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60377&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceedings of the National`
  line `Committee, the Authority and the State Committee shall be invalid merely by reason of—`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Authority; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Authority not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (60372)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60372&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or`
  line `any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line
  line `(a) the time and place of the meetings of the National Committee and the procedure to be`
  line `followed at such meetings under sub-section (1) of section 7 and the expenditure incurred on the`
  line `meetings of the National Committee under sub-section (3) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) the qualifications and experience of the officers and other employee of the Authority in the`
  line `field of dam safety or such other field under sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(c) the functions, powers, and terms and conditions of service of other officers and other`
  line `employees of the Authority under sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be made by the Central Government by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (60373)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60373&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification,`
  line `make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or`
  line `any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line
  line `(a) the times and places of the meetings of the State Committee and the procedure to be`
  line `followed at such meetings under sub-section (1) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(b) the expenditure incurred on the meetings of the State Committee under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 13;`
  line
  line `(c) the fee and allowances paid to the specialist members or expert invitees of the State`
  line `Committee or its sub-committees under sub-section (4) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(d) the organisational structure and work procedure of State Dam Safety Organisation under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(e) the qualifications and experience of the officers and other employees of the State Dam`
  line `Safety Organisation in the field of dam safety or such other field under sub-section (1) of section`
  line 15;
  line
  line `(f) the functions, powers, and terms and conditions of service of the employees of the State Dam`
  line `Safety Organisation under sub-section (2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(g) the dam safety measures in respect of dams other than specified dams under section 46;`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be made by the State Government by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by a State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before the State Legislature, where it consists of two Houses, or where such legislature`
  line `consists of one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (60374)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Power to make regulations by Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60374&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority on the recommendations of the`
  line `National Committee may make regulations consistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder to`
  line `carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations`
  line `may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line
  line `(a) the guidelines, standards and other directions for achieving the satisfactory level of dam`
  line `safety assurance under sub-section (1) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(b) the vulnerability and hazard classification criteria of specified dams under section 17;`
  line
  line `(c) the details and form pertaining to the maintenance of log books or database under subsection (1) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(d) the qualifications, experience and training of the individuals responsible for safety of`
  line `specified dams under section 23;`
  line
  line `(e) the employment of competent engineers and their qualifications and experience for the`
  line `purpose of investigation, design and construction of specified dams under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 26;`
  line
  line `(f) the quality control measures for the purpose of dam construction under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 26;`
  line
  line `(g) the level of competent engineers for the dam safety units under section 30;`
  line
  line `(h) the guidelines and check-lists for inspection of specified dams under clause (a) of subsection (3) of section 31;`
  line
  line `(i) the minimum number of set of instrumentations in the specified dams and the manner of their`
  line `installation under sub-section (1) of section 32;`
  line
  line `(j) the form, manner and time interval for forwarding the analysis of readings to the State Dam`
  line `Safety Organisation under sub-section (2) of section 32;`
  line
  line `(k) the data requirements of hydro-meteorological stations in the vicinity of specified dams`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(l) the data requirements of seismological stations in the vicinity of specified dams under subsection (1) of section 34;`
  line
  line `(m) the suitable location and manner of collection, compliance, process and storage of data`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 34;`
  line
  line `(n) the time interval of risk assessment studies to be carried out under sub-section (2) of section`
  line 35;
  line
  line `(o) time interval for updating the emergency action plan under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 36;`
  line
  line `(p) the time interval for the comprehensive safety evaluation of specified dams under subsection (1) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(q) the mandatory review of design flood of existing specified dams under clause (b) of subsection (2) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(r) the mandatory site specific seismic parameter studies of existing specified dams under clause`
  line `(c) of sub-section (2) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(s) the measures necessary to ensure dam safety by every owner of dam other than specified`
  line `dams under section 46;`
  line
  line `(t) any other matter which is to be specified or in respect of which provision is to be made by`
  line `the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (60375)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60375&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or regulation or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be`
  line `made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect,`
  line `as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to`
  line `the validity of anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (60376)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892&sectionId=60376&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_199_1516_00001_202141_1641277357892
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such`
  line `provisions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear it to be necessary or`
  line `expedient for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three years from the date`
  line `of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
